items.title: Awesome Neovim
items.content_text:
### Tree-sitter Supported Colorscheme / Diagnostics

*   [askfiy/visual\_studio\_code (⭐204)](https://github.com/askfiy/visual_studio_code) - A Neovim theme that highly restores vscode, so that your friends will no longer be surprised that you use Neovim, because they will think you are using vscode.
*   [cryptomilk/nightcity.nvim (⭐66)](https://github.com/cryptomilk/nightcity.nvim) - A dark colorscheme inspired by Inkpot, Jellybeans, Gruvbox and Tokyonight with LSP support.

### Utility / Diagnostics

*   [sontungexpt/url-open (⭐100)](https://github.com/sontungexpt/url-open) - Open URLs under the cursor and create highlight effects for them.

### Terminal Integration / Diagnostics

*   [willothy/wezterm.nvim (⭐233)](https://github.com/willothy/wezterm.nvim) - Functions for interacting with Wezterm.
*   [mikesmithgh/kitty-scrollback.nvim (⭐662)](https://github.com/mikesmithgh/kitty-scrollback.nvim) - Open your Kitty scrollback buffer. Ameowzing.

items.title: Awesome Python Data Science
items.content_text: ### Reinforcement Learning / Others * [Gymnasium (⭐9.6k)](https://github.com/Farama-Foundation/Gymnasium) - An API standard for single-agent reinforcement learning environments, with popular reference environments and related utilities (formerly [Gym (⭐36k)](https://github.com/openai/gym)). * [Stable Baselines3 (⭐11k)](https://github.com/DLR-RM/stable-baselines3) - A set of improved implementations of reinforcement learning algorithms based on OpenAI Baselines. * [RLlib](https://ray.readthedocs.io/en/latest/rllib.html) - Scalable Reinforcement Learning. * [Acme (⭐3.7k)](https://github.com/google-deepmind/acme) - A library of reinforcement learning components and agents. * [d3rlpy (⭐1.5k)](https://github.com/takuseno/d3rlpy) - An offline deep reinforcement learning library. * [TRFL (⭐3.1k)](https://github.com/deepmind/trfl) - TensorFlow Reinforcement Learning. * [Dopamine (⭐11k)](https://github.com/google/dopamine) - A research framework for fast prototyping of reinforcement learning algorithms. * [keras-rl (⭐5.6k)](https://github.com/keras-rl/keras-rl) - Deep Reinforcement Learning for Keras. * [garage (⭐2k)](https://github.com/rlworkgroup/garage) - A toolkit for reproducible reinforcement learning research. * [Horizon (⭐3.6k)](https://github.com/facebookresearch/Horizon) - A platform for Applied Reinforcement Learning. ### Graph Machine Learning / Others * [pytorch\_geometric (⭐23k)](https://github.com/rusty1s/pytorch_geometric) - Geometric Deep Learning Extension Library for PyTorch. * [pytorch\_geometric\_temporal (⭐2.8k)](https://github.com/benedekrozemberczki/pytorch_geometric_temporal) - Temporal Extension Library for PyTorch Geometric. * [Spektral (⭐2.4k)](https://github.com/danielegrattarola/spektral) - Deep learning on graphs. * [Karate Club (⭐2.2k)](https://github.com/benedekrozemberczki/karateclub) - An unsupervised machine learning library for graph-structured data. * [Little Ball of Fur (⭐710)](https://github.com/benedekrozemberczki/littleballoffur) - A library for sampling graph structured data. ### Probabilistic Graphical Models / Others * [pgmpy (⭐3k)](https://github.com/pgmpy/pgmpy) - A python library for working with Probabilistic Graphical Models. * [pyAgrum](https://agrum.gitlab.io/) - A GRaphical Universal Modeler. ### Probabilistic Methods / Others * [pyro (⭐8.8k)](https://github.com/uber/pyro) - A flexible, scalable deep probabilistic programming library built on PyTorch. * [PyMC (⭐9.1k)](https://github.com/pymc-devs/pymc) - Bayesian Stochastic Modelling in Python. * [ZhuSuan](http://zhusuan.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) - Bayesian Deep Learning. * [GPflow](http://gpflow.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest) - Gaussian processes in TensorFlow. * [InferPy (⭐148)](https://github.com/PGM-Lab/InferPy) - Deep Probabilistic Modelling Made Easy. * [PyStan (⭐354)](https://github.com/stan-dev/pystan) - Bayesian inference using the No-U-Turn sampler (Python interface). * [sklearn-bayes (⭐519)](https://github.com/AmazaspShumik/sklearn-bayes) - Python package for Bayesian Machine Learning with scikit-learn API. * [skpro (⭐271)](https://github.com/alan-turing-institute/skpro) - Supervised domain-agnostic prediction framework for probabilistic modelling by [The Alan Turing Institute](https://www.turing.ac.uk/). * [PyVarInf (⭐359)](https://github.com/ctallec/pyvarinf) - Bayesian Deep Learning methods with Variational Inference for PyTorch. * [emcee (⭐1.5k)](https://github.com/dfm/emcee) - The Python ensemble sampling toolkit for affine-invariant MCMC. * [hsmmlearn (⭐85)](https://github.com/jvkersch/hsmmlearn) - A library for hidden semi-Markov models with explicit durations. * [pyhsmm (⭐560)](https://github.com/mattjj/pyhsmm) - Bayesian inference in HSMMs and HMMs. * [GPyTorch (⭐3.7k)](https://github.com/cornellius-gp/gpytorch) - A highly efficient and modular implementation of Gaussian Processes in PyTorch. * [sklearn-crfsuite (⭐431)](https://github.com/TeamHG-Memex/sklearn-crfsuite) - A scikit-learn-inspired API for CRFsuite. ### Web Scraping / Synthetic Data * [BeautifulSoup](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/): The easiest library to scrape static websites for beginners * [Scrapy](https://scrapy.org/): Fast and extensible scraping library. Can write rules and create customized scraper without touching the core * [Selenium](https://selenium-python.readthedocs.io/installation.html#introduction): Use Selenium Python API to access all functionalities of Selenium WebDriver in an intuitive way like a real user. * [Pattern (⭐8.8k)](https://github.com/clips/pattern): High level scraping for well-establish websites such as Google, Twitter, and Wikipedia. Also has NLP, machine learning algorithms, and visualization * [twitterscraper (⭐2.5k)](https://github.com/taspinar/twitterscraper): Efficient library to scrape Twitter
items.content_html:
Reinforcement Learning / Others

  • Gymnasium (⭐9.6k) - An API standard for single-agent reinforcement learning environments, with popular reference environments and related utilities (formerly Gym (⭐36k)).
  • Stable Baselines3 (⭐11k) - A set of improved implementations of reinforcement learning algorithms based on OpenAI Baselines.
  • RLlib - Scalable Reinforcement Learning.
  • Acme (⭐3.7k) - A library of reinforcement learning components and agents.
  • d3rlpy (⭐1.5k) - An offline deep reinforcement learning library.
  • TRFL (⭐3.1k) - TensorFlow Reinforcement Learning.
  • Dopamine (⭐11k) - A research framework for fast prototyping of reinforcement learning algorithms.
  • keras-rl (⭐5.6k) - Deep Reinforcement Learning for Keras.
  • garage (⭐2k) - A toolkit for reproducible reinforcement learning research.
  • Horizon (⭐3.6k) - A platform for Applied Reinforcement Learning.

Graph Machine Learning / Others

  • pytorch_geometric (⭐23k) - Geometric Deep Learning Extension Library for PyTorch.
  • pytorch_geometric_temporal (⭐2.8k) - Temporal Extension Library for PyTorch Geometric.
  • Spektral (⭐2.4k) - Deep learning on graphs.
  • Karate Club (⭐2.2k) - An unsupervised machine learning library for graph-structured data.
  • Little Ball of Fur (⭐710) - A library for sampling graph structured data.

Probabilistic Graphical Models / Others

  • pgmpy (⭐3k) - A python library for working with Probabilistic Graphical Models.
  • pyAgrum - A GRaphical Universal Modeler.

Probabilistic Methods / Others

  • pyro (⭐8.8k) - A flexible, scalable deep probabilistic programming library built on PyTorch.
  • PyMC (⭐9.1k) - Bayesian Stochastic Modelling in Python.
  • ZhuSuan - Bayesian Deep Learning.
  • GPflow - Gaussian processes in TensorFlow.
  • InferPy (⭐148) - Deep Probabilistic Modelling Made Easy.
  • PyStan (⭐354) - Bayesian inference using the No-U-Turn sampler (Python interface).
  • sklearn-bayes (⭐519) - Python package for Bayesian Machine Learning with scikit-learn API.
  • skpro (⭐271) - Supervised domain-agnostic prediction framework for probabilistic modelling by The Alan Turing Institute.
  • PyVarInf (⭐359) - Bayesian Deep Learning methods with Variational Inference for PyTorch.
  • emcee (⭐1.5k) - The Python ensemble sampling toolkit for affine-invariant MCMC.
  • hsmmlearn (⭐85) - A library for hidden semi-Markov models with explicit durations.
  • pyhsmm (⭐560) - Bayesian inference in HSMMs and HMMs.
  • GPyTorch (⭐3.7k) - A highly efficient and modular implementation of Gaussian Processes in PyTorch.
  • sklearn-crfsuite (⭐431) - A scikit-learn-inspired API for CRFsuite.

Web Scraping / Synthetic Data

  • BeautifulSoup: The easiest library to scrape static websites for beginners
  • Scrapy: Fast and extensible scraping library. Can write rules and create customized scraper without touching the core
  • Selenium: Use Selenium Python API to access all functionalities of Selenium WebDriver in an intuitive way like a real user.
  • Pattern (⭐8.8k): High level scraping for well-establish websites such as Google, Twitter, and Wikipedia. Also has NLP, machine learning algorithms, and visualization
  • twitterscraper (⭐2.5k): Efficient library to scrape Twitter
